did.unittitle: Rockefeller University records, Campus Office Biographical Files

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The Rockefeller University (formerly Rockefeller Institute for Medical Research), Campus Office Biographical Files, contains biographical information about Rockefeller professors, researchers, trustees, administrators, and other employees from its founding in 1901 through the early 2000s.

Many of the files contain newspaper clippings, published works, press releases from the University's Public Relations Office, photographs, negatives, curriculum vitas, and obituaries. Files that date from the 1920s through the 1940s may contain written applications for fellowships at the Institute.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Audio-visal materials (photographs, negatives, and slides) have been removed from their original folder and filed in a separate folder immediately following the original folder. These files are often, but not always, labeled as "A" folders.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Files are predominantly arranged alphabetically by last name, or institutional name.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: This collection was processed by Bethany J. Antos and Christine D'Alessandro and was completed in August 2010.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: For materials related to faculty, staff, and others associated with the Institute/University, please consult FA260 Rockefeller University records, Scientific Staff Biographical Files.
Larger collections may be available for some individuals. Consult Archivist for further assistance.
